<script language='javascript'>
function firstAppointmentCheck() {
  if(document.itinerary != undefined) 
  	document.itinerary.startingaddress.disabled = document.itinerary.firstappointmentstart.checked;
}
function move(change, index) {
	document.itinerary.change.value = change;
	document.itinerary.index.value = index;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

function highlightRow(row,onOff) {
	color = onOff ? 'lightgreen' : 'white';
	key = row.id.split('_');
	key = key[0];
	//alert(key);
	document.getElementById(key+'_top').style.background = color;
	for(var i=0; document.getElementById(key+'_'+i); i++)
	  document.getElementById(key+'_'+i).style.background = color;
}

function generateDirections() {
	
	//alert("Temporarily unavailable.");
	//return;
	
	document.itinerary.generate.value = 1;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

function sendToProvider() {
	document.itinerary.generate.value = 0;
	document.itinerary.emailprovider.value = 1;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

firstAppointmentCheck();
</script>

<br>(A) Daily dog walk visits should be cancelled twenty-four (24) hours before the scheduled Services are to be performed. Visits cancelled less than twenty-four (24) hours in advance may be charged the full price of the Service scheduled.
<br>

Vacation visits and/or ROVERnights cancelled less than three (3) days in advance may be charged 50% of scheduled fee. It is in Company&rsquo;s sole discretion to waive any applicable cancellation fees.

We do ask that you notify us as soon as you know there may be a cancellation. Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled care to be paid. With the exception of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of 
the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. We request your understanding that holiday travel is a peak service time for pet care. <br>Early Returns/Last minute Changes: It is not unusual for trip plans to change at the last minute. However, please understand that Wet Noses Pet Sitting carefully schedules our time to service you and our other clients. Please contact us as soon as you know or suspect there will be a change to your 
plans. Visits must be canceled before 4pm the day prior to the service in order to receive a credit. Visits canceled after this time will not receive credit for their visit.  Same day cancellations will not receive credit for any unneeded visits.   
<br>
<br>Cancellations: Normally cancellations are not a problem for Wet Noses Pet Sitting prior to 4 days of the beginning of your scheduled appointment. We do ask that you notify us as soon as you know there may be a cancellation. Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled care to be paid. With the exception of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of 
the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. We request your understanding that holiday travel is a peak service time for pet care. If you appointment is cancelled during these times your credit card will be charged with your cancellation fee.  </span><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://leashtime.com/style.css" type="text/css" />

Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled care to be paid. With the exception of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of 
the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. We request your understanding that holiday travel is a peak service time for pet care. If you appointment is cancelled during these times your credit card will be charged with your cancellation fee.  </span><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://leashtime.com/style.css" type="text/css" />

<br>
<br>Early Returns/Last minute Changes: It is not unusual for trip plans to change at the last minute. However, please understand that Wet Noses Pet Sitting carefully schedules our time to service you and our other clients. Please contact us as soon as you know or suspect there will be a change to your 
plans. Visits must be canceled before 4pm the day prior to the service in order to receive a credit. Visits canceled after this time will not receive credit for their visit.  Same day cancellations will not receive credit for any unneeded visits.   
<br>
<br>Cancellations: Normally cancellations are not a problem for Wet Noses Pet Sitting prior to 4 days of the beginning of your scheduled appointment. We do ask that you notify us as soon as you know there may be a cancellation. Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled care to be paid. With the exception of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of 
the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. We request your understanding that holiday travel is a peak service time for pet care. If you appointment is cancelled during these times your credit card will be charged with your cancellation fee.  </span><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://leashtime.com/style.css" type="text/css" />

agreement/policies<br>-Enter client/pet profile information in detail<p>LeashTime is also used for scheduling, sending general messages, and/or providing special instructions and notices. <p><h2 style="color:red"><b>K9 KREWE POLICIES</b></h2><p><b><u>Communication Policy</u></b><br>Business communications between K9 Krewe and clients must be executed through the following methods only: <p><b>1) Phone calls/voicemail (our preferred method for general communication; calls/voicemails receive the quickest responses)</b><p>2) In-person <p>3) Written Correspondence sent thru LeashTime (must be logged in). <br><span style="color:blue"><b>ANY and ALL <I>written</I> communication, including general messages, service schedule requests, notices of temporary changes or situation, notices of long term changes/updates regarding the status of your pets/home, etc. <u>MUST BE SUBMITTED <I> SOLELY</I> 
thru your LeashTime account</u></b></span>.<p>             <span style="color:red"> <b>***<u>Sending   TEXT  MESSAGES &amp; EMAILS to K9 Krewe are <b>NOT    PERMITTED.</u>***</b></span><p></b>K9 Krewe only accepts <i>written</i> correspondence via LEASHTIME for many reasons. Limiting <I>written</I> communications to ONE, web accessible source (LeashTime) enables a streamlined, organized workflow; Each time you/K9 Krewe submits a message <u>thru LeashTime</u>, the system automatically adds a record of the message to the account.<br>Note:  When you receive K9 Krewe emails in your inbox which contain a schedule confirmation request, general message, etc, the message has been processed thru LeashTime, even though the message may <i>appear</I> to have been sent via gmail.  <p>If you submit a general message, inquiry, or service request, please allow up to <u>three business days,</u> to receive a 
response.  <p>We may periodically post a photo or video update on your pet(s) on our Facebook page.  Please  "like"/share our page and visit often!  Comments/post shares are welcomed, encouraged, and appreciated! <p><br><b><u>Cancellation Policies</u></b> <p>With each reservation, <u>we make a commitment to you,</u> the client, to provide the requested services on the reserved dates. As a result, other reservation requests may be turned away.<p><p style="color:blue">- <b>Canceling Overnight Stay Pet Sitting:</b><p>Cancellations made <b>30 days or less before the start date</b> of the reserved Overnight Stay Pet Sitting: NO refunds or credits. <p><p style="color:green"><b>- Canceling Non-Overnight Pet Sitting and Recess Visits:</b><p>1) <i>Except for holiday season dates,</i> cancellations made <b>14 days or less before the start date</b> of the reserved Non-Overnight Pet Sitting/Recess 
Visits: NO refunds or credits. <p>2) Holiday season dates: cancellations made <b>30 or less days before the start date</b> of the reserved Non-Overnight Pet Sitting/Recess Visits: NO refunds or credits.<p><p style="color:deepskyblue"><b> - Canceling Training Sessions and Adventure Daycare:</b><p>1) Except for holiday season dates, cancellations made 7 business days or less before the date of the scheduled Training Session or Adventure Daycare: NO refunds or credits.<p>2) Holiday season dates: Training Sessions and Adventure Daycare cancellations made 14 or fewer days before the scheduled date of service: NO refunds or credits.<p><b><u>Safe Arrival Home Confirmation Policy (Applies to Pet Sitting services only)</u></b><p>To ensure that your pets receive the necessary care beyond the last scheduled visit, K9 Krewe requires that clients confirm their safe arrival home after each trip. <p>AS 
SOON AS client arrives safely at their home, he/she must <u>confirm his/her safe arrival by calling</u> K9 Krewe at 225-364-9247, regardless of the time, night or day. In the event that K9 Krewe is unable to answer the call, clients are to leave a <u>voicemail</u> stating that they've arrived safely at their home. <u>Text messages and emails are NOT accepted.</u> Unless we hear from the client or someone on his/her behalf at least one hour before the start time of when the next visit would be needed (based on the same interval &amp; frequency of visits that were originally scheduled), visits will continue and client will be billed for all additional visits made. <p><br><b><u>Last Minute Service Request Policy</u></b><p><u>Last minute service requests must submitted by the client by logging into LeashTime.</u> <i>However, an additional step is required if you are submitting a request for 
services that are need to begin within seven days of the request date:</i>  <u>clients must <b>call</b> K9 Krewe once the last minute request has been submitted.</u>  This is to give clients as much time as possible to make other arrangements on short notice, in the event that K9 Krewe is booked up, or otherwise unavailable.  <p><br><b>Before the Start Date of Every Reservation:</b><p>Before the start date of every reservation, please ensure that you have reviewed your LeashTime profile/credit card info to ensure all is up to date. We will assume your profile is accurate and must disregard any instructions left at your home (exception: photos showing desired grooming style are ok). <p><p style="color:orange"><u>If you need to provide us with special instructions <i>that differ from the normal routine instructions</i> that are listed on your profile (whether it's regarding your pets or

SUBJECT:         Visit Cancellation Same Day and Weekends

Hi Sophie, <p>We've received your request to cancel your scheduled visit. <p>On weekdays, for same day cancellations, the deadline for cancellations is 8am. You will be charged for the cost of the walk or visit for any cancellations made after that time on the day of your requested service. If you reach us before 8am on weekdays, you can cancel with no additional fee. <p>For weekends, the deadline for cancellations is 5:30pm on the Friday afternoon prior as we finalize weekend staffing and scheduling based on availability. As long as you reach us by 5:30pm on Friday afternoon, you will not be charged for your walk or visit. <br>Thanks!

calendar Days for Holiday or Overnight Reservations</li><br></ul><p><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c"><em>NO REFUND AFTER DATES LISTED BELOW OR IF SERVICE HAS STARTED</strong> </em>  <p><ul style="line-height: 1.1"><br><li><strong>Daily/Mid-day Visits:</strong>  If less than <strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">two (2) business days </strong></span> notice prior to the first visit is given, no refund will be issued, and in the event that payment has not yet been made, TLC will bill Client. </li><br><li><strong>Holidays and Overnight Bookings: </strong> If less than <strong><span style="color: #c91c1c"> five (5) business days </strong></span> notice prior to the first visit is given, no refund will be issued, and in the event that payment has not yet been made, TLC will bill the Client.<br></li><br><li><strong>Dog Walking:</strong> Cancellation made for <strong><span style="color: 
#c91c1c">Same day TLC will retain 50% of the visit for that day.</li><br></ul><p><br><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">SURCHARGES:</strong></span><br><ul style="line-height: 1.1"><br><li>Holidays- listed on contract</li> <br><li><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">Last minute reservation less than (3) three business days for Daily/Mid-day</strong> </span></li> <br><li><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">Last minute reservation less than (7) Business days for holidays and Overnight care</strong> </span></li> <br><li>Pickup and dropping off keys in person</li>  <br><li>Less than (3) three days&rsquo; notice to meet sitter for a consult before you depart</li><br><li>Emergency vet visits to vet&rsquo;s office </li><br><li>Additional consults requested after initial, and adding pets to the family</li><br></ul><p><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">POLICY:</strong></span><p>If you would like to 
review any of the policies, they are all explained in detail in our <a href="https://tlcpetsitter.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/TLC-Client-Handbook-1.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: #c91c1c">Client Handbook</a>.<p><br><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">TIPS:</span></strong><p>Gratuities are always appreciated. Visits</li><br><li><strong>14 calendar Days for Holiday or Overnight Reservations</li><br></ul><p><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c"><em>NO REFUND AFTER DATES LISTED BELOW OR IF SERVICE HAS STARTED</strong> </em>  <p><ul style="line-height: 1.1"><br><li><strong>Daily/Mid-day Visits:</strong>  If less than <strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">two (2) business days </strong></span> notice prior to the first visit is given, no refund will be issued, and in the event that payment has not yet been made, TLC will bill Client. </li><br><li><strong>Holidays and Overnight Bookings: </strong> If less than <strong><span style="color: #c91c1c"> five (5) business days </strong></span> notice prior to the first visit is given, no refund will be issued, and in the event that payment has not yet been made, TLC will bill the Client.<br></li><br><li><strong>Dog Walking:</strong> Cancellation made for 
<strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">Same day TLC will retain 50% of the visit for that day.</li><br></ul><p><br><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">SURCHARGES:</strong></span><br><ul style="line-height: 1.1"><br><li>Holidays- listed on contract</li> <br><li><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">Last minute reservation less than (3) three business days for Daily/Mid-day</strong> </span></li> <br><li><strong><span style="color: #c91c1c">Last minute reservation less than (7) Business days for holidays and Overnight care</strong> </span></li> <br><li>Pickup and dropping off keys in person</li>  <br><li>Less than (3) three days&rsquo; notice to meet sitter for a consult before you depart</li><br><li>Emergency vet visits to vet&rsquo;s office </li><br><li>Additional consults requested after initial, and adding pets to the family</li><br></ul><p><strong><span style="color:

Using LeashTime ensures that you receive an email confirmation once an appointment has been accepted or cancelled, and it will also help prevent any scheduling errors. For last minute requests and/or cancellations (i.e., the day of the walk/visit), evening and/or weekend walks, and house sitting requests, we ask that you also please email us at pets@HouseBrokenNY.com and/or call us to verify your request has been received and can be accommodated.  <p>Please note that the following surcharges may apply to your requested service:<p>o   Requesting a service 
after 6:00pm the day before the service is to be performed - $5 will be charged to your account. Walks/visits on weekends will have a $6 surcharge added to the base price of the service. Walks/visits on holidays will have a $7 or $10 surcharge added to the base price of 
the service (depending on the holiday). Solo walks/visits (i.e., you don't want us to pair your dog up with another dog) will have a $5 surcharge added to the base price of the service. <p>We require our clients to enroll in bi-weekly automatic payments with their credit card to avoid service interruptions. Unfortunately, we are unable to maintain client account balances of more than two weeks worth of services at a time. You will receive an itemized receipt (via email) for services rendered at the time your credit card is charged.<p>For more detailed information on our policies and rates, please visit our website (www.HouseBrokenNY.com).<p>We look forward to walking Julep, and thank you for choosing HouseBroken for your pet care needs.<p><br>Vivian and the HouseBroken Team

plans. Visits must be canceled before 4pm the day prior to the service in order to receive a credit. Visits canceled after this time will not receive credit for their visit.  Same day cancellations will not receive credit for any unneeded visits.   
<br>
<br>Cancellations: Normally cancellations are not a problem for Wet Noses Pet Sitting prior to 4 days of the beginning of your scheduled appointment. We do ask that you notify us as soon as you know there may be a cancellation. Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled care to be paid. With the exception of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of 
the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. We request your understanding that holiday travel is a peak service time for pet care. Returns/Last minute Changes: It is not unusual for trip plans to change at the last minute. Please contact us as soon as you know or suspect there will be a change to your plans. Visits must be canceled before 4pm the day prior to the service in order to receive a credit. Visits canceled after this time will not receive credit for their visit.  Same day cancellations will not receive credit for any unneeded visits.   
<br>
<br>Cancellations: Normally cancellations are not a problem for Wet Noses Pet Sitting prior to 4 days of the beginning of your scheduled appointment. We do ask that you notify us as soon as you know there may be a cancellation. Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled 
care to be paid. With the exception of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. We request your understanding that holiday travel is a peak service time for pet care. Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled care to be paid. With the exception 
of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. SUBJECT:         Your Invoice

<img src='https://leashtime.com/bizfiles/biz_617/logo.png' ><br>Hi Ezra Watland,<p>Here is your latest invoice. Payment is due before service begins. We do not accept checks or cash payment.<p>If you require additional services, such a medication, daily updates, or photos, please submit requests prior to processing your payment.<p>Frequent travelers will be billed on the first of each month; bimonthly billing will be issued on the 15th and charged subsequently. <p>New client short notice schedule requests will be charged automatically with no further action required. <p>Payment options:<br>For security purposes CKS does not have access to your credit card information and cannot process cards unless they are submitted by the client through Leashtime.<p>Option 1. Click the Pay Now button attached to this invoice and input your card number. PLEASE DO NOT CLICK PAY NOW BUTTON MORE THAN ONCE. 
You will be responsible for transaction fees should CKS refund double payments.<p>Option 2. When adding/updating your cc in Leashtime, select Auto Payment, and no further action is required. <p>Option 3: Select No Auto Payment if you do not authorize CKS to process your payment without written consent. By choosing this option, you are responsible for processing your payment before your pet sits begins. Outstanding invoices will be billed 20% interest after 30 days and 30% after 60 days. Accounts not paid within 90 days of services rendered, will be frozen.<p>Gratuity-<br>Gratuity is customary and reflects your appreciation for the purrific service our sitters provide to you. You may leave a cash tip or check addressed to your sitter in your home, or gratuity may be added through Leashtime using the drop-down service menu. Once registered, you will be able to do the following from the comfort of your laptop or smart phone. <p>	- Make reservation requests<br>        - Get notifications from your sitter as visits are completed<br>        - Update your pets&rsquo; individual information<br>        - Update information about your home<br>	- Instant Billing Totals<p>Following this email, you will be receiving another email asking you to change your password. Even though you may not have an immediate need for pet sitting we recommend you go ahead and set up your account at your earliest convenience. That way it will be ready 
to go when you need us.<p>We will continue to be available to assist anyone not comfortable with on line reservations via phone, text or email.<p>Office Hours Monday &ndash; Friday 8:00am &ndash; 5:00pm<p>Requests coming in after hours and over the weekends will be handled the following business day. Although we do not guarantee last minute availability, in event of emergency, you can still text me and/or your pet sitter. <p>You will now be receiving your Invoices via email through LeashTime rather than the Pet Sitter leaving a paper copy. Please check your Invoice for accuracy and let us know of any discrepancies. You have several options for payment: click the &ldquo;pay online&rdquo; button on your emailed invoice to pay via credit card, save your credit card information in your LeastTime profile and authorize auto pay, leave a check on the counter for your sitter or mail your check directly to our 
office (please make note of the visit dates on your check). LeashTime is a secure site and your credit card number is encrypted so no one can view the full number. Payments are then processed through Authorize.net, which is a secure gateway. Please note that if you pay by check, there will be some delay before your account is credited so there is a chance that you will receive a duplicate invoice. We are asking you please DO NOT LEAVE CASH for your payment unless it is for the Pet Sitters as a tip over and above the Invoice amount. <p>We apologize for any inconvenience and look forward to a more streamlined system! We hope this will make us more efficient in serving you better! We appreciate you and love your 4 legged family members! <p>Wishing you happy and safe travels with no worries about your pets and home!<p>Barbara Foster, Cell 704.641.0557<br>Amy Weeks, Office Manager, Cell

ask that you notify us as soon as you know there may be a cancellation. Any cancellations within the 4 days prior to your appointment will result in a 50% of the total invoice for the scheduled care to be paid. With the exception of severe weather, life threatening emergencies or a death in the family, any cancellations prior to a major holiday; ie: Christmas, New Years, Easter, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day and Thanksgiving with less than a seven day notice will result in 50% of the total invoice for scheduled pet care to be paid. SUCCESS: <166431821307.13920.11981739333322146715@525552-web2.leashtime.com>

SENT: Tue, 27 Sep 2022 18:36:53 -0400
FROM:                info@thepetgurl.com
TO:                       michaeljeschawitz43@gmail.com
SUBJECT:         Using our online system- The Pet GurL

Thank you for choosing The Pet GurL! We are excited to spend time with your furry babies and look forward to a long standing relationship!<p>You have hopefully had a chance to login to our online system by now.  You can access this at any time by going to our site at www.thepetgurl.com and clicking on the Client Login button.  This is an important part of how our business is run so we rely on clients input into our system in order to always provide the best service we can.  This information is for your benefit so you can know how to use the system for keeping your pet&rsquo;s information up to date, inputting your schedule, and even paying online.<p>To start, when you first login to our system,  our terms come up and you will have to agree in order to move forward.  If you have any questions about this, always let us know.  From there you will have full access to your own profile.  We ask 
that you look over each section of the profile to add any information you feel will be helpful to the sitter.  We will also go in and add notes from the initial meeting but there are times that something isn&rsquo;t discussed or even miscommunicated at the consult and having you keeping up with your profile will ensure that we always have the most up to date information.<p>The next and very important part of our online system is the scheduling part.  We ask that our clients take the time to learn this part as it guarantees that your visits will always be taken care of by someone on our team.  Your sitter may be on vacation or not available and contacting them directly will not always guarantee visits but using our online scheduling system will.<p>How do I schedule?<p>  <p>When you login to your profile, go to request visit and click on the link.  You can select the entire date range for 
which you know the visits at this time.  If you only know of two visits a month apart, that&rsquo;s OK.  You can select your range to include both visits and just select the two days you need and no visits on the other days in between.  If you are unsure on what service to select, you can click here (http://www.thepetgurl.com/how-to-request-visits/) to look at a description of services.  There is also a video from our software company that walks your through scheduling, although not our exact site, the instructions are the same. You will also select a time frame from the list as well.  We give a window of time for visits and typically go over your schedule and request during our meeting but you can also leave a note of preferred time(s) in the note section below your schedule and we will do our best to work with this.  Please keep in mind that the more notice you can give, the better as we 
are running on full days 365 days a year.  Any notes that you think may be helpful can go into the note section as well. After this, you will submit your request and it will go to our office for approval.  Once approved, we will send an email confirmation and your schedule will show up when you login on your home page.  You can also cancel or make changes on your schedule at any time.  Please also note that if you select the wrong service, or pricing looks different than what you were expecting, that&rsquo;s OK. We can easily adjust after it is entered and your email confirmation will show the final price and it may not be the same as what you saw on the schedule when you were submitting it.  As long as you get it entered, we can adjust as needed at any point.<p>PAYMENT<p>We setup payment a few different ways, depending on what type of service you go with.  You can check for an invoice under 
the E-PAYMENT  tab.  If you see an invoice, then you can click on it and pay directly from there by clicking the PAY NOW link.  This will link you to Paypal and allow you to pay whatever the amount on the invoice is.  There are situations where you may want to pay an amount different from the invoice and if this happens, you can use the link on our home page of our main site that says PAY HERE (www.thepetgurl.com/payment)  This doesn&rsquo;t limit you to the amount on the invoice and can be used for upfront payments, gratuity added to bill, or any other situation where you want to pay a different amount.  <p>So there you have it! We can help you get started and if you have any questions, email info@thepetgurl.com at any point.  Our office will take care of any billing and scheduling issues while your sitter will be providing the best care possible for your babies. We work together to bring 
you a great experience and are always here to help!  Thanks again for choosing The Pet GurL! Also make sure to find us on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram and you may see your furry friends during their time with us.  <p>Sincerely,<br>The Pet GurL Team<br>

function firstAppointmentCheck() {
  if(document.itinerary != undefined) 
  	document.itinerary.startingaddress.disabled = document.itinerary.firstappointmentstart.checked;
}
function move(change, index) {
	document.itinerary.change.value = change;
	document.itinerary.index.value = index;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

function highlightRow(row,onOff) {
	color = onOff ? 'lightgreen' : 'white';
	key = row.id.split('_');
	key = key[0];
	//alert(key);
	document.getElementById(key+'_top').style.background = color;
	for(var i=0; document.getElementById(key+'_'+i); i++)
	  document.getElementById(key+'_'+i).style.background = color;
}

function generateDirections() {
	
	//alert("Temporarily unavailable.");
	//return;
	
	document.itinerary.generate.value = 1;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

function sendToProvider() {
	document.itinerary.generate.value = 0;
	document.itinerary.emailprovider.value = 1;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

firstAppointmentCheck();
</script>

<script language='javascript'>
function firstAppointmentCheck() {
  if(document.itinerary != undefined) 
  	document.itinerary.startingaddress.disabled = document.itinerary.firstappointmentstart.checked;
}
function move(change, index) {
	document.itinerary.change.value = change;
	document.itinerary.index.value = index;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

function highlightRow(row,onOff) {
	color = onOff ? 'lightgreen' : 'white';
	key = row.id.split('_');
	key = key[0];
	//alert(key);
	document.getElementById(key+'_top').style.background = color;
	for(var i=0; document.getElementById(key+'_'+i); i++)
	  document.getElementById(key+'_'+i).style.background = color;
}

function generateDirections() {
	
	//alert("Temporarily unavailable.");
	//return;
	
	document.itinerary.generate.value = 1;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

function sendToProvider() {
	document.itinerary.generate.value = 0;
	document.itinerary.emailprovider.value = 1;
	document.itinerary.submit();
}

firstAppointmentCheck();
</script>

Accounts not paid within 90 days of services rendered, will be frozen.<p>Gratuity-<br>Gratuity is customary and reflects your appreciation for the purrific service our sitters provide to you. For Campgrounds, there is an office.  They will know where you are located

Our office can not text on the landline. And make sure your emergency people know how to contact you while away. <p>ALSO, if you are away and there is any kind of statewide problem here in NH, like blizzard, power outage, loss of phone service, etc.  Make sure to "like" our business Facebook page (find the link on our website). We will post on our page any messages in these kind of emergencies. For example - Halloween 2012 we had a blizzard, 
lost power, telephone and internet for a week. We were able to post on our Facebook page that all pets in our care were visited, cared for and fine. Giving you all peace of mind while you were away. <p>4. Follow our medication/supplement/herb protocol.  If it was not sent to you, please ask for it.  <br>All Pet Care changes should be in your online profile, but please alert the sitter and office to all new changes.<p>Remember that we go by the pet care information you have entered ONLINE (not in 
notes, etc.)<br>Pet care must be approved by office, in case there are any questions, etc.  <p>Remember - when updating or changing any information online, that your changes come to our office and we approve.  <br>Once approved, Then you will see your changes and updates on your profile.  Please, Give at least 24 hours to see those changes online.<p>5. ALARMS and ANYONE ALLOWED ON YOUR PROPERTY OR IN YOUR HOME WHILE YOU ARE AWAY<p>Alarms are ALL different.  If you choose to have an active alarm while you are away, please be advised that we will set it off (once or multiple times).  Review the Alarm section in our Service Agreement.<p>Anyone be allowed in your home or on your property while you are away this time? <br>We must know names, phone numbers and when they may come.<br>Please don't give our sitters a heart attack with unknown people or having police come if people are okay to be 
there. Notify our office know AND leave a note for the sitter of the name and phone number of all people who will be on your property or in your home while you are away.  <p>Any person coming in at anytime we are scheduled to care for pets, and is also caring for pets, releases our company, employees and owner of any and all liability with pet care.  We can not control what others do or do not do.<p>Any person who will be on your property or in your home while we are scheduled, releases our company, employees and owner of any and all liability for any situation. <p>6. CHANGES TO RESERVATION<p>If you need to make ANY CHANGES to your schedule and it is less than 48 hours for these changes, in any emergency, you must go online first to your schedule.  Then send an email, then leave a voice message. In the event of no power, internet and phone, we may not get your changes and the sitter will 
go according to the current schedule. Any cancellations of any visits within your reservation within 14 days of your start date will result in no refund or credit.  <p>7. PLEASE EMAIL US WHEN YOU GET HOME<p>We would love a return home email to our office, just letting us know you have returned home safely and that your pets are now in your care. Unfortunately, many people do forget to notify us, so, We do stop pet care at the end of your reservation, however, if you need us to continue for ANY reason, don't hesitate to let us know. We would be happy to make sure your pets are cared for. <p>8.  IF YOU RETURN HOME EARLY &ndash; <p>if you return home early, before your scheduled reservation is done, please, still email and/or call our office but in case the office may not be able to inform the sitter before she comes for your next scheduled visit.  If you wish for the sitter to NOT enter your 
home (unless she gets that the visit is scheduled, she must go in to care for pets, even if there is a car in the driveway, because many people allow neighbors to park in driveways), put a NOTE on your door, letting the pet sitter know you are home and there is no need to come in.  <p>9.  WHAT DO I DO IF I CAN NOT RETURN HOME ON TIME, FLIGHT CANCELLED/DELAYED, EMERGENCY, ETC.?<p>You must first book ONLINE, then send an email, third - call our office and leave a message.  If you do not have access to the internet, call someone who does so they can book it for you.  If we are not in the office, we will not get your message until the next morning.  By covering both the online booking or even sending an email, we may get that sooner but if we are in the office for another emergency for a client or simply working, we may get your voice mail sooner.  Best to do all THREE to ensure we will get 
it last minute.  <p>10. PACKAGES AND MAIL<br>If you will be expecting any packages or important mail while you are away, let us know.<br>We will be happy to bring in any packages and mail that is delivered that we see, however some delivery people put packages in out of the way places, so we may not see them.  Unfortunately, we are there for pet care and only bring in packages and mail as a courtesy. We will not be responsible for any packages or mail delivered in any way.<p>We have had a huge lazy boy chair delivered once while we were petsitting, with heavy rains scheduled to come in.  it was very heavy and awkward and did not easily fit through the door.  Unfortunately, we can not be responsible.  It took TWO pet sitters and almost an hour to get it inside because it was oversized.  We will not be able to do this in the future.  So, please make arrangements for a neighbor or friend to 
accept delivery.<p>We have also had packages delivered that needed to be placed in a refrigerator or freezer right away.  We are very happy to do this if the ENTIRE UNOPENED box will fit in the refrigerator or freezer.  We can not rearrange your refrigerator or freezer for the box to fit.  We can NOT open any packages to make items fit.   We will not be responsible for any items that need to be refrigerated or frozen.<p>It will be your responsibility to arrange for these packages to be delivered after you arrive home or have a friend, neighbor or relative stop by to take care of it.   <p>If we must contact you via email or phone, and it is OUTSIDE of our call back times, there will be an extra charge for the office to to do this.<p>Remember, our service is not package or mail delivery.  We will take a few seconds to bring items inside but can not do anything that will require more then a 
few seconds and can not lift heavy packages.<p>********************************************************<p>EXAMPLE OF YOUR EMERGENCY EMAIL TO US - <p>1 - Leaving Approx. 5AM ON Monday, April 21.
